Sample Alert Report – True Positive

Alert Title: Suspicious Privilege Escalation Detected

Alert ID: SOC-TP-001

Alert Severity: High

Alert Status: True Positive – Escalated to L2

Who
•	User Account: j.doe
•	Role: Standard User
•	Host: FIN-WKS-23
•	Operating System: Windows 10

What
The user account j.doe executed a command that added the account to the local Administrators group.
This action was performed without a corresponding approved change request or IT maintenance window.
Command observed: net localgroup administrators j.doe /add

When
•	Start Time: 2025-01-14 10:42 UTC
•	End Time: 2025-01-14 10:43 UTC

Where
•	Endpoint: FIN-WKS-23
•	Source IP: 10.20.15.33 (Internal Network)

Why (Verdict Reasoning)
The activity represents an unauthorized privilege escalation attempt.
Verification with the IT team confirmed that no administrative privileges were approved for this user at the time of execution.
This behavior is consistent with potential account compromise or insider threat activity.

Actions Taken
•	Alert documented with full investigation details
•	IT team contacted to validate authorization (no approval found)
•	Alert escalated to L2 for further investigation and remediation

Escalation Reason
•	High-risk activity requiring account review and potential containment
•	Possible credential compromise
•	Remediation actions (password reset / host review) required

Recommendations
•	Immediate password reset for the affected user
•	Review recent authentication logs for lateral movement
•	Assess endpoint for additional suspicious activity

